paragraph.content:
it shall not matter whether the laws of the Parties place the offence
                    within the same category of offence or denominate the offence by the same
                    terminology;

subparagraph.content:
any offence which, by reason of a multilateral international agreement,
                        the Parties must not treat as a political offence or an offence connected
                        with a political offence;

paragraph.content:
when the person sought has been finally convicted or acquitted by the
                    Requested Party for the offence for which the person’s surrender is
                    requested;

when the prosecution or the punishment for the offence for which surrender
                    is requested would be barred by reasons prescribed under the law of either Party
                    including a law relating to the lapse of time;

as accurate a description as possible of the person sought, together with
                    any other information which would help to establish the person’s identity and
                    nationality including, if known, his or her whereabouts;

subparagraph.content:
if the person was convicted but not sentenced, a statement to that
                        effect by the appropriate court and a copy of the warrant of arrest;
                        or

paragraph.content:
an equivalent or lesser offence, however described, based on the facts in
                    respect of which his surrender was granted, provided such offence is one for
                    which he could be surrendered under this Agreement;

Obtaining property or pecuniary advantage by deception; theft; robbery;
                burglary (including breaking and entering) or similar offences; embezzlement;
                blackmail; extortion; handling or receiving stolen property; false accounting; any
                other offence in respect of property or fiscal matters involving fraud; any offence
                against the law relating to unlawful deprivation of property.
